{{Character infobox | name = Ekyannus III | titles = [[Shriah]] | nicknames = The Golden | appearances = mentioned only | lived = 2432 - 2516 | race = [[Men]] | ethnicity = | nationality = | gender = Male | occupation = Shriah of the [[Thousand Temples]] | relatives = }}
'''Ekyannus III''', “the Golden,” was [[Shriah]] of the [[Thousand Temples]]. He is famous for converting his friend [[Triamis the Great]] to [[Inrithism]] in 2505, thus resulting in Inrithism being declared the official state religion of the [[Ceneian Empire]]. This led to Inrithism becoming the dominant religion in the [[Three Seas]].<ref>Encyclopedic Glossary, ‘Ekyannus III’</ref>
==References== <references /> [[Category:Shriahs]] [[Category:Thousand Temples]] [[Category:Men]] [[Category:Characters from the Three Seas]]

{{Character infobox | name = Zarathinius | titles = | nicknames = | appearances = mentioned only | lived = 3688 - 3745 | race = [[Men]] | ethnicity = | nationality = | gender = Male | occupation = [[Sorcerer]] | relatives = }}
'''Zarathinius''' is the famed author of ''[[A Defence of the Arcane Arts]],'' a criticism of the [[Inrithism|Inrithi]] prohibition of [[sorcery]] and of Inrithism itself.<ref>Encyclopedic Glossary, ‘Zarathinius’</ref> While widely cited by philosophers and sorcerers, the work is banned by the [[Thousand Temples]].<ref>Encyclopedic Glossary, ''‘Defence of the Arcane Arts, A’''</ref>
==References== <references /> [[Category:Sorcerers]] [[Category:Writers]] [[Category:Philosophers]] [[Category:Characters from the Three Seas]] [[Category:Men]]

{{Character infobox | name = Sarothesser I | titles = King | nicknames = | appearances = mentioned only | lived = 3317 - 3402 | race = [[Men]] | ethnicity = Ketyai | nationality = [[Ainon]]i | gender = Male | occupation = King of High Ainon | relatives = }}
'''Sarothesser I''' was the founder of [[High Ainon]], who overthrew the yoke of the [[Ceneian Empire]] in 3372 and ascended the Assurkamp Throne as the first Ainoni King.<ref>Encyclopedic Glossary, 'Sarothesser I'</ref>
