==References== <references/> [[Category:Wracu]] [[Category:Characters from Golgotterath]]

'''''On the Folly of Men''''' is the magnum opus of the famed satirist [[Ontillas]].{{EG|On the Folly of Men}}

==Excerpts==
“There are three, and only three, kinds of men in the world: cynics, fanatics, and [[Mandate]] Schoolmen.”{{1|1}}

“Men are forever pointing at others, which is why I always follow the knuckle and not the nail.”{{2|13}}

“They strike down the weak and call it justice. They ungird their loins and call it reparation. They bark like dogs and call it reason.”{{2|24}}

“Of course we make crutches of one another. Why else would we crawl when we lose our lovers?”{{3|6}}

“As a miller once told me, when the gears do not meet, they become as teeth. So it is with men and their machinations.”{{3|11}}

