{{Character infobox | name = Paro Inrau | image = [[Image:Inrau_by_quintvc-d84nkmh.png|260px]] | caption = Inrau by [http://quintvc.deviantart.com/ Quinthane] | titles = | nicknames = | lived = 4088 - 4110 | race = [[Men]] | ethnicity = [[Ketyai]] | nationality = [[Nron]]i | gender = Male | occupation = Shrial Priest | relatives = | appearances = ''[[The Darkness That Comes Before]]'' }}
'''Paro Inrau''' is a former student of [[Drusas Achamian]], slain in [[Sumna]].{{EG|Inrau, Paro}}
==Appearance== Inrau is dark-haired, slender, and clean-shaven. He has large brown eyes and feminine lips.{{1|4}}
==Story== ===''What Came Before''=== Achamian took on Inrau as a student, training him to become a member of the [[Mandate]]; however, Inrau decided not to join the Mandate and to become a [[Shrial Priest]] of the [[Thousand Temples]] instead. Defection from the Mandate is normally punished by death, but Achamian arranged for Inrau’s escape.
===''The Darkness That Comes Before''=== Achamian is instructed by his superiors to use Inrau as an informant to learn more about [[Maithanet]] and his [[Holy War]]. Shortly after agreeing to help Achamian, Inrau is confronted by two [[skin-spies]], [[Mujonish]] and [[Cutias Sarcellus]], and a [[Consult]] [[Synthese]]. Inrau destroys Mujonish, but realizes he is outmatched by the Synthese, and jumps to his death rather than risk giving up valuable information when it threatens him with the [[Agonies]].
==References== <references /> [[Category:POV characters]] [[Category:Ketyai]] [[Category:Characters from Nron]] [[Category:Mandate]] [[Category:Thousand Temples]] [[Category:Priests]] [[Category:Gnostic sorcerers]]

